# OboxSTEAM — Project Context & Domain Reference

> Load this file when working on feature logic, data modelling, routing, roles, or portfolio/subdomain behaviour. For code style use `nextjs-engineering-rule.mdc`; for colors and UI use `styling-rule.mdc`.

---

## Project Overview

**OboxSTEAM** is a Vietnamese edtech platform that sells and delivers STEAM experiential learning programs (like a leaner Coursera + physical lab sessions). Its distinguishing feature is that every enrolled student automatically builds a **digital Portfolio** — a public microsite documenting their learning journey — which they can use for overseas university applications.

**Core value loop:**
Student enrolls in program → learns through online/offline sessions → evidence is collected automatically → AI processes evidence → Portfolio microsite is generated → student shares it with universities

---

## Actors & Roles

| Actor | Key Permissions |
|-------|----------------|
| **Guest** | Browse programs, view public student portfolios |
| **Student** | Enroll, learn, track progress, manage own portfolio |
| **Parent** | Register on behalf of child, pay, monitor child's progress (linked sub-profile) |
| **Mentor / Instructor** | Teach sessions, grade students per stage, upload recommendation letters, upload evidence media |
| **Provider** | Partner education center that hosts programs on the platform; approves Mentor accounts |
| **Manager** | OboxSTEAM platform representative; quality-controls Providers |
| **Admin** | System-level observer; manages users, content, AI pipelines |

**Parent–Child linking:** A parent account can create multiple child (Student) sub-profiles. All child activity triggers real-time notifications to the parent.

**Mentor approval flow:** Mentor registers → uploads CCCD, degree, CV, language cert → Provider reviews → approved.

