## Content Hierarchy

```
Program
└── Curriculum Framework        (teaching syllabus, has unlock conditions)
    └── Module                  (themed unit; has prerequisites)
        └── Course              (theory docs + task list; reusable across modules)
            └── Activity        (a concrete task the student must complete)
```

- A **Module** is locked until all prerequisite modules are passed. Failed prerequisite → student can re-enroll in that module only.
- A **Course** contains theory materials + required activities. Activities are the atomic unit of student work.
- **Program enrollment** gives the student a personal Curriculum instance (their own progress tracked separately from others).

