## Core Features

### 3.1 Authentication & Account Management
- Multi-channel sign-up: Google OAuth, phone (OTP), email/password.
- Role selection at registration (Student, Parent, Mentor).
- Mentor accounts require Provider approval with document upload.
- Parent can create and manage child sub-profiles; activity notifications flow to parent.

### 3.2 Student Profile (Portfolio Data Source)
The profile is the raw data the AI uses to build the portfolio. Key sections:

**Academic info:** current school, grade, intended major direction, target study-abroad country & year, GPA (overall + STEM subjects), standardized test scores (SAT/ACT/AP/IB), language certificates (IELTS/TOEFL).

**Achievements:** awards/competitions (especially Robotics, Informatics, ISEF), project roles, extracurriculars auto-pulled from enrolled programs.

**STEAM evidence:** featured projects (student selects 3–5 proudest), community service linked to STEAM, field trips and workshops auto-counted from system.

**Skills:** hard skills list, soft skills list.

**Written content:** personal bio (250–500 words), stage reflections journal (AI summarises into Portfolio), recommendation letters uploaded by Mentors.

**Media:** auto-tagged photo library (AI face recognition), short highlight video links (9:16, AI-generated from session footage).

### 3.3 Learning Journey (LMS — built in-house)
- Online sessions: embedded video lectures + live class links (e.g. Google Meet), auto-attendance.
- Offline sessions: physical lab / field trip; Mentor uploads session photos/video → AI tags students → evidence auto-routed to student portfolio.
- Stage timeline with start/end dates; system alerts on delay.
- Per-activity student report form: self-assessment of knowledge gained.
- Mentor evaluation per stage: Excellent / Pass / Needs Improvement.
- Auto progress report sent to parent after each stage.
- Past stage review: student can revisit completed stages to see materials, evidence, and evaluations.

### 3.4 Certificates
- Auto-generated E-Certificate PDF on program completion.
- Sub-certificates per module or milestone.
- Certificates feed automatically into the Portfolio.

### 3.5 Portfolio & Personal Microsite
- Aggregates all certificates, AI videos, mentor assessments from all programs into one master portfolio.
- Skills radar/bar chart auto-generated from completed courses.
- Student can manually add additional credentials/achievements.
- Customisable layout: student picks a template; can write personal statement and set slogan.

**Portfolio Plans:**

| Plan | URL format | PDF export | Templates | Privacy |
|------|-----------|-----------|-----------|---------|
| Standard (free) | `obox.id/{student-id}` | View online only | Default templates | Public link |
| Premium (paid) | `{name}.obox.id` | Unlimited PDF download | Premium templates + custom branding (colors, slogan) | Public link |

**Subdomain architecture (Premium):**
- Wildcard DNS `*.obox.id` points to the Next.js app.
- `middleware.ts` reads `request.headers.host`, extracts subdomain, rewrites internally to `/(portfolio-site)/[username]`.
- Route group `(portfolio-site)` has its own minimal layout (no main nav).

### 3.6 AI Features
- **Face recognition:** AI scans uploaded session photos/videos → identifies students → auto-tags and routes evidence to their individual portfolio store.
- **Highlight reel generation:** AI cuts session footage into short 9:16 clips per student → stored in student media library.
- **Reflection summarisation:** AI reads student journal entries → generates polished summary prose for the Portfolio.
- **Skills analysis:** AI analyses completed courses → generates percentage scores per skill dimension.

> AI feature implementation is backend/service responsibility. Frontend consumes the results via API. Do not implement AI logic on the frontend.

