## Tech Stack

| Layer | Choice |
|-------|--------|
| Framework | Next.js 16 (App Router, Turbopack) |
| Language | TypeScript (strict) |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS v4 + shadcn/ui (base-nova style) |
| Animation components | React Bits (via shadcn MCP registry) |
| State | Redux Toolkit (global auth/UI); Server Components for server data |
| Validation | Zod v4 — `z.string().url()` pattern for env; shared schemas in `lib/validations/` |
| Forms | react-hook-form + @hookform/resolvers/zod |
| Package manager | pnpm only |
| Icons | Lucide React (sparingly) |
| Fonts | Nunito (headings), Inter (body), JetBrains Mono (code) |

---

## Key Conventions

- `app/(main)/` for all authenticated platform pages; `app/(auth)/` for sign-in flows; `app/(portfolio-site)/` for public portfolio microsites.
- Server Components by default; `"use client"` only for interactive leaves.
- Redux slices live in `store/slices/`; typed hooks in `store/hooks.ts`.
- API call wrappers go in `lib/api/`; Zod schemas in `lib/validations/`.
- STEAM category colors (`--steam-science`, `--steam-technology`, etc.) are CSS variables — use `text-steam-science`, `bg-steam-technology` etc. as Tailwind utilities.
- Student data is sensitive — never log PII; server-only API keys via env vars.

